# Yarn 1 (classic) config for the web/ app.
#
# TEMPORARY: skip the engines compatibility check on install.
# Prisma 7 (and @prisma/client) support our Node 20.19.4, but a transitive dep
# (@prisma/streams-local, pulled via @prisma/dev — the unused `prisma dev` local server)
# declares Node >=22, and Yarn 1 enforces engines for all packages. Without this, a plain
# `yarn install` aborts with "incompatible module".
#
# Remove this once we move to Node 22 (>=22.12) — tracked as a deferred follow-up to retiring
# the root Vite app (see context/project-overview.md §16). On Node 22.12+ the check passes natively.
ignore-engines true
